# Runtime/state at REPO ROOT only — safe to push without leaking local runs
#
# WHY `/memory/` (leading slash) and NOT `memory/` everywhere:
# A bare `memory/` pattern ignores every path segment named `memory/` anywhere in the
# tree — including the Python package `src/sage/memory/` (RAG, layers, code). That
# would silently untrack production source. Root-only `/memory/` ignores the
# generated workspace dir (`memory/system_state.json`, handoff, session logs, RL
# artifacts, …) while leaving `src/sage/memory/` tracked.
#
# Why we do NOT commit that root `memory/` folder to GitHub: it is per-machine,
# per-session state (not product source). It changes every run, may include paths,
# prompts, and logs you do not want public or in PR noise.
/memory/

/datasets/
bench*.json
*_out.json
*.log

# Local experiment / scratch at repo root (not the package)
bench_out.txt

# Large reference trees (not the SAGE product source)
simialr stuff/

# Editable install metadata
src/*.egg-info/
*.egg-info/

# Local planning drafts (optional)
plan v1/
plan v2/
plan final/

# Local architecture spec / planning folder
sage plan/

# Staging dir for long docs (optional)
.spec_staging/

# SAGE per-project local UI (rules under `.sage/` are often committed; chats are not)
.sage/chat_sessions/

# IDE/editor
.vscode/
.idea/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Keep docs tracked (including evidence docs)
!docs/
